	<h1>Create Your Own Recipe</h1>
	<p style="color:red">What fields are in the form depends on what the API looks like. For ingredients and steps, maybe we can ask for the user for the # of steps/ingredients then we can loop to create matching # of text boxes???</p>
	<form method="POST" action="">
		Name of Dish: <input type="text" id="name" /><br/><br/>
		Category: 
		<select name="cuisine_type" size="1">
			<option value="italian">Italian</option>
			<option value="carribbean">Carribbean</option>
			<option value="korean">Korean</option>
			<option value="german">German</option>
			<option value="indian">Indian</option>
			<option value="others">Others</option>
		</select><br/><br/>
		Preparation Time: 
		<select name="prep_time" size="1">
			<option value="15">less than 15 mins</option>
			<option value="30">less than 30 mins</option>
			<option value="60">between 30 mins and 1 hr</option>
			<option value="120">between 1 hr and 2 hrs</option>
			<option value="more">more than 2 hrs</option>
		</select><br/><br/>
		Ingredients: <input type="text" id="ingredients" /><br/><br/>
		Steps: <input type="text" id="steps" /><br/><br/>
		<input type="submit" value="Add to Favorites" /><br/><br/>
	</form>
</body>
